<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-02-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-02-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="1579" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1579">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 701.5212/1a.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister to
                                    Mexico</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-03">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 3, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>431. Department informed by Spanish Embassy here that Angel Caso,
                                Special Representative of Spanish Government near General Villa, now
                                in Mexico City, threatened with arrest by Carranza forces.</p>
                            <p>Please confer with appropriate authorities and point out to them the
                                serious consequences that may result from the arrest of a diplomatic
                                officer of a foreign government and strenuously protest against such
                                action. Mr. Silliman may be of service in matter in view of his
                                friendly relations with General Carranza.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>